Popular Ghanian Actor, John Dumelo has expressed his excitement at seeing Nigerian Afro Beats star, Davido perform at the Qatar 2022 World Cup draw on Friday. According to the actor who made this known via his verified Twitter handle, seeing Davido perform at the FIFA World Cup stage made him proud as an African. He wrote: “I’m really happy for Davido. Seeing him perform on stage at the FIFA World Cup event really made me proud as an African.” It would be recalled that the Nigerian national team, the Super Eagles recently lost out on securing the ticket after losing to their West African neighbours Ghana in the playoffs to the Qatar 2022 World Cup after playing a 1-1 draw on aggregate at both Kumasi and Abuja respectively. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state… Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…